ugh Deleuze, and how Deleuze's thought can be experimented upon and re-designed to produce new concepts. This book taps into the emerging networks between philosophy as an act of inventing concepts and design as the process of inventing the world.List of ContributorsBetti MarenkoJamie BrassettManola AntonioliAnne SauvagnarguesT. Hugh CrawfordBetti MarenkoDerek HalesVincent BeauboisJohn O’ReillyPetra Hroch"  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aDesignxPhilosophy. 4aPhilosophy. 7aARCHITECTURE / Criticism.2bisacsh1 aAntonioli, Manola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeaubois, Vincent, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrassett, Jamie, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBrassett, Jamie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrawford, T. Hugh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHales, Derek, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHroch, Petra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarenko, Betti, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Reilly, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSauvagnargues, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311078045140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978074869155540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748691555423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748691555/original  a978-3-11-078045-1  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_AD  aEBA_EEBKALL  aE